                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>At their 32d meeting on November 23, the <gloss target="#t_NATO1">NATO</gloss>
                    Council Deputies considered a resolution on Berlin introduced by United States
                    Deputy <pb facs="0916" n="900" xml:id="pg_900"/> Spofford, and agreed that each
                    country should consider the level of its trade with the city. The Deputies also
                    agreed “that an attack on German police or any other force in Western Berlin
                    would constitute attack on occupying powers and bring <gloss target="#t_NATO1"
                        >NATO</gloss> into force.” (Depto 213, November 23, from London, not
                    printed, 740.5/11–2350)</p>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
